    "name": "eL Hotel Yogyakarta Malioboro",
    "detail": "Everything is great! Property looks very new and very nice. Car parking seems sufficient (or it is well-managed by hotel security/gatekeeper staff). Professional service from all staff (gatekeeper, bellboy, receptionist), they are very helpful and full of service mind. The room is still in new condition and clean; bath room amenities is up to standard. Elevator and corridors are also clean. There is an area under construction but it is not obstruct nor disturb our stay. The only thing I find unpleasant is the light at the open closet (cloth hanging) that it is automatically on at all time when you put the key card on. We asked receptionist and were informed that it will be turned off only when the keycard is off. I found this unpleasant because I was not comfortable sleeping with the light (though my roommate consider that is minimal to dim light and she slept well!!). In conclusion, this is a perfect choice of hotel we selected in Yogyakarta. Recommended!!",
